    },
    {
      "key": {
        "uuid": "9ab29df4_7a0e3536",
        "filename": "firmware/buflib.c",
        "patchSetId": 1
      },
      "lineNbr": 231,
      "author": {
        "id": 1000020
      },
      "writtenOn": "2014-01-11T11:02:21Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "The only reason AFAIK is that crc_32() is used to protect eeprom saved settings integrity and empty eeprom is all 0xff\u0027s.",
      "parentUuid": "9ab29df4_1afff902",
      "revId": "fd3c0ff7dbb759199c23efc1e246176ad93aabd0",
      "serverId": "583131e1-1a33-4f2b-b8ec-82434880f207",
      "unresolved": false
    },
    {
      "key": {
        "uuid": "9ab29df4_fa19657a",
        "filename": "firmware/buflib.c",
        "patchSetId": 1
      },
      "lineNbr": 231,
      "author": {
        "id": 1000004
      },
      "writtenOn": "2014-01-11T11:06:33Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "It\u0027s common practice for CRC in general to use 0xffffffff as initial (not specific to rockbox or eeproms, also in ethernet for example). However, as I said, it doesnt really matter. The initial does not affect the error-detecting properties of CRC.",
      "parentUuid": "9ab29df4_7a0e3536",
      "revId": "fd3c0ff7dbb759199c23efc1e246176ad93aabd0",
      "serverId": "583131e1-1a33-4f2b-b8ec-82434880f207",
      "unresolved": false
    },
